## Acceptance Criteria

- [x] `_DisplayMixin` exists in `src/burnt/core/_display.py`
- [x] `CostEstimate` inherits from `_DisplayMixin` and has working `display()`
- [x] `SimulationResult` inherits from `_DisplayMixin` and has working `display()`
- [x] `MultiSimulationResult` inherits from `_DisplayMixin` and has working `display()`
- [x] `MultiSimulationResult.best()` returns the lowest-cost named scenario
- [x] `ClusterRecommendation` inherits from `_DisplayMixin` and has working `display()`
- [x] `ClusterRecommendation.to_api_json()` returns `self.balanced.to_api_json()`
- [x] `AdvisoryReport` uses `_DisplayMixin` (no duplicated `_is_databricks_notebook()`)
- [x] All `display()` calls fall back to `print()` when neither `rich` nor `IPython` available
- [x] No `ImportError` raised in any environment
- [x] `.to_markdown()` implemented on `CostEstimate`, `SimulationResult`, `MultiSimulationResult`, `ClusterRecommendation`, `AdvisoryReport` — output is valid GFM markdown
- [x] `.to_markdown()` output contains no HTML tags
- [x] Progress feedback fires during `estimate()` in multi-tier mode; suppressed in offline-only mode
- [x] Progress feedback is a graceful no-op when `rich` and `IPython` are both absent

